{
  "id": "019d286a-f2d8-78b2-92cd-41891498aea7",
  "content": "## Root Causes\n\n### 1. Broken cross-file import resolution (D72)\n\n`resolve_rust_module_path()` in `treesitter.rs` returns the **current file path** for all `crate::` and `super::` imports instead of resolving to the target module's file. This means `use crate::config::CorviaConfig` in `main.rs` creates a self-loop (`main.rs → main.rs`) instead of a cross-file edge (`main.rs → config.rs`).\n\n\n### 2. Markdown chunks have zero relations (D73)\n\n`MarkdownChunker::chunk()` returns `relations: vec![]`. Documentation that references code files and types (via backtick code spans, links, and code blocks) creates no graph edges. ~600 markdown chunks across 37 doc files are graph-isolated.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-04-m3.4-graph-edge-improvements-design.md",
